# Prometheus `authorization.credentials_file` for scraping the ADMIN-gated /actuator/prometheus (M5).
#
# Copy this file to `metrics_authz` (no extension) in this directory and replace the placeholder
# below with the base64 of "<admin-user>:<admin-password>" - i.e. the value half of
# THEBULLPEN_ADMIN_BASIC_AUTH - with NO trailing newline:
#
#   printf '%s' "$THEBULLPEN_ADMIN_BASIC_AUTH" | base64 | tr -d '\n' > metrics_authz
#
# The real `metrics_authz` is gitignored; only this `.example` is committed. The secrets dir is
# mounted read-only at /etc/prometheus/secrets (see infra/docker-compose.yml). Prometheus sends it
# verbatim as `Authorization: Basic <contents>`, which the app's SecurityConfig accepts as the ADMIN
# credential. (Comment lines are fine here because Prometheus never reads `.example`, only the real
# `metrics_authz`; the real file must contain ONLY the base64 string.)
REPLACE_WITH_BASE64_OF_ADMINUSER_COLON_PASSWORD
